  "text": "If p 0 = |Y 0 | = n + 1, a linear model rather than an underdetermined quadratic model is built for each function. The reason is that, despite both having error bounds that are linear in ∆ for the first derivatives, the error bound for the latter includes also the norm of the model Hessian, as stated in Lemma 2.2 in [CITATION_1] , which makes it worse than the former.",
